Dialogs.Dialog: Nene
By the way, did you know that our school used to have a tea house？
Eh？ Is that so？
Yeah, and girls could go there to learn tea ceremony and flower arranging.
Hmm, but I wonder if any girls still want to learn them now. They are quite old traditions...
Oh, you don't know anything about girls.
Deep in girls' hearts, they yearn to be more girlish.
It doesn't matter if it's an old or a new tradition.
Is that so？
Yes. Tea ceremony and flower arranging have long history and they both are beautiful traditions.
Girls are sensitive to beauty, you know？
In other words... It's the same feeling as when they want to be pretty？
Well, it might be so. Hehe, do you understand girls more now？
You really have to learn a lot more, okay？
Nene
Do you remember that we talked about the tea house earlier？
Yeah, girls who wanted to learn traditional ceremonies would go there, right？
Yeah, and the one who taught them was the classical literature teacher.
Huh？ It's that teacher？ Where is she now？
I think she has retired already. And the room hasn't been used, so it was remodeled.
Hmm. That seems like such a waste.
A waste？
Yeah. If that teacher were still here, I might have a chance to watch ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ in the tea ceremony.
Hehe, I wonder.
But, if I have a chance, I might try to learn it...
Yeah, when I think about it, this is quite regrettable.
Nene
Do you remember we talked about the classical literature teacher last time？
Yeah, you said she retired already, right？
Yeah. Even after she retired, students have continued using the tea house.
So, they have a new teacher then？
It seems so. Actually, the previous teacher was only a lecturer, but this new one seems to be a professional.
Eh...？ In that case, you can learn how to do it the professional way, huh？
Hey... You said earlier that you wanted to see me in a tea ceremony, right？
I did, but... Don't tell me...
Yeah, I've been thinking whether I should take the class. What do you think？
I wanted to say that you should, but... Are you gonna be okay？ This class must be very strict.
It'd be a lie if I say that I don't feel uneasy about it, but...
But, you seem to yearn for an ideal Japanese woman...
Nene
Last time, I told you about the tea ceremony course...
Yeah, did you apply for it in the end？
I didn't. Actually, I already checked it out and the monthly tuition fee is very high.
To think about it, that's quite natural for such a course. But I can't afford it.
...I see. It's a little disappointing, huh？
No, I'm fine.
...But, you've been thinking about it for a while...
It's not like I was dying to learn it. I just wanted to try and that's all.
Is that so...？
And I just realized one important thing.
What is it？
If I took that course, we wouldn't be able to spend time together after school.
(So, that's your reason, huh？)
Nene
I was cleaning the teaching material storage room earlier and I found something interesting.
Huh？ What is it？
It's a map of this area in the old days.
Even the social studies teacher wasn't aware of its existence.
When we examined it, it happened to be more than a hundred years old.
That's amazing. I wonder what were around here during that time.
The area where our school located was actually... a large cemetery.
...Really？
Not really. Sorry, I was kidding. Actually, it used to be a forest. That's quite boring.
Well, so that's what our school used to be.
But, I find it fun. Maybe I should show it to you if I have a chance.
But the symbols on the map are different from the current ones, so they are difficult to understand.
Hmm. If you find anything interesting from it, let me know too, okay？
Nene
Do you remember the old map we talked about？
Yeah, the hundred-year-old map of this area, right？
Yeah. I looked at it again when I cleaned that room.
Did you figure out something？
Well, what do you think the location of Dixie's used to be in the past？
...A cemetery？
Geez... No. It used to be a big residence.
Residence？
Yeah, it was a very big house with a store built as a separate building.
Although the buildings were built separately, they were still in the same big residence.
Hmm？ ...Then the owner must be very rich.
That seemed so. Now, the social studies teacher has become interested in this. She said she'd do some research about it.
If I know some more info, I'll tell you. Hehe.
Hey, did you find out anything new about the old residence we were talking about？
Nene
Ah, yeah...
Eh？ What's wrong？
The social studies teacher researched about it, but... it turned out to be such a sad story.
Is that so...？ What kind of story？
The daughter of that residence's owner had a lover. But her parents didn't approve them and forced them to separate.
...Things like that happened a lot in the past, right？ Especially with rich people.
Yeah... But, the daughter couldn't stand the shock and fell ill...
Then the residence's owner put her in one building and wouldn't let anyone see her.
Whoa, that's cruel... Wasn't that like a confinement？
And we're working at the place where that residence used to be... Hah...
Nene
▲主人公＊▲. Wait a minute！
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, what's wrong？
We were talking about the separation earlier...
Yeah, that sad story, right？
Actually, after some study, I found that there was a sequel to that.
A sequel？
Yeah. That guy who was forced to be separated from the residence owner's daughter came back some years later.
Eh？
He had been working very hard and succeeded in his business... Then he asked for permission to become the daughter's husband.
And？
Of course, they could finally become together. That's how it should be, right？
...Ah, we're working at such a wonderful place. I'm very impressed.
Anyway... ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲. This reaction is totally the opposite of last time, huh...
Nene
Hey, have you ever bought lunch at our school's store？
Yeah, I have.
I've heard that it's a very high competition. Is that true？
That rumor's been around. There's a very famous sandwich that's always sold out in no time.
Hmm？ Which one is that？
Hmm, I don't know exactly. But... I think it might be the tonkatsu sandwich because it sells so well.
Ah, I've heard about it. The guy in my class bought it from another student.
He bought it from a student？
Since it's very famous, some people buy and sell it as a premium item.
So... You can sell it like that？ Wow, that sounds great.
If people wanted to eat it that much, this tonkatsu sandwich must be really delicious.
Nene
Hey, hey. I had eaten that famous tonkatsu sandwich, you know.
Eh？ How was it then？
Well... It was delicious, but...
The size was a little too big. And I felt like it was quite oily.
I see. That's why it seems to be very popular for the guys in the sports club.
Well, for people who use a lot of energy, it would suit them. I think it was made for guys.
Hmm...？ But, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, how could you buy it？ The store is always very crowded.
Hehe... I asked someone else to buy it for me.
...W-Who？
It's a secret. Hehe. You don't have to worry about who bought it for me. It wasn't my boyfriend.
Y-You don't have to tell me that. Your boyfriend is here...
Don't worry. You're getting jealous for something like this. ...So cute▼
Hey, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲...
Nene
Hmm？ Eh？ What's wrong？ You seem to be worried about something.
Do you remember... when we talked about the tonkatsu sandwich earlier？
Of course. It was delicious and the size was big.
Not that... But about who bought it...
Ah... Hehe. Do you care about it？
Yeah, I do. It would be too difficult for a girl to fight the crowd and buy it for you, so...
So... what？
So, that person must be a guy, right？ Don't tell me to stop worrying about it, because I can't.
Geez. I have only you. Why can't you trust me？ You make this big sister sad.
(Even if you say it like that, it doesn't work. ...I'm really concerned about it！)
Hey, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲. About the tonkatsu sandwich...
Nene
Are you still worried about it？ It was really nothing.
Don't hide it from me. I've been so worried that I even lost my appetite lately.
Really？
Yeah...
Is that so...？ Well... It was the teacher.
No way... Don't tell me that ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ and the teacher are...
No, no. It's not what you think.
I went to see the teacher during lunch break and he happened to be eating the tonkatsu sandwich. So, I asked if I could try it.
Is that so...？ Somehow, I'm relieved.
Ah... So you were really concerned. Was I really bad？ Maybe I should get a tonkatsu sandwich for you as an apology.
(I've had enough with this tonkatsu sandwich...)
Nene
It might be sudden but I have a question for you. Don't be shy and just answer me honestly, okay？
W-What are you talking about？
Do you like a girl in a school uniform？ Yes or No？ Answer me.
What kind of question is this？
Just answer me. I just want to know your tastes, so tell me honestly.
For something like that... It's both "yes" and "no"...
That's not allowed. You must choose one. I won't get mad, okay？
Hmm... Well, it actually depends on the types of the uniforms, but if I have to choose...
What's your answer？
Well... Y-Yes... I think...
I see. As I thought. Hah...
(W-What actually was that question about though？)
Well, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲. About what you asked me earlier, what was that？
Nene
What I asked you？ What？
Come on. You asked whether I like girls in uniforms.
Ah, that. What was it...？ Do you want to know？
Yeah, sort of. Because you asked me, I was a bit concerned.
Hmm... But don't laugh if I tell you, okay？
I won't laugh.
Then... Ah, I shouldn't tell you. I know you'll laugh for sure.
(I won't laugh... She really won't tell me, huh？ Hmm, now I'm even more curious.)
Nene
Hey, I have another question for you.
Another one？ What is it this time？
Did you know that there's a new school at the next train station？
Eh？ Really？ I didn't know that.
Really？ A lot of students from that school get off at this station. You don't notice？
Not at all.
I see... That's fine then. Ah, but they came to the restaurant we work at, too. Are you sure you don't know？
I said I don't know... Well, how's that school's uniform look like？ I might have some clues...
I really can't tell you that... I feel like girls from that school are my rivals. I can't tell you.
(▲姉ヶ崎＊▲. What are you talking about！？)
Hey, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲. About the new school...
Nene
No way... You've seen those uniforms already？
The uniforms with red plaid skirts and yellow cardigans？
Yes... Ah, you saw them at last.
What's wrong with them？ I don't think the design is weird or anything.
Not weird...？ That was a foul play. They deserve yellow cards.
F-Foul play？ Yellow card？
Their skirts are too short. That causes troubles for guys, right？ What would happen to male teachers there？
(Ah... Speaking of which, the skirts are really short.)
I think it's bad for those young girls to wear something like that. They should wait until they grow older.
(Young girls？ They are also high school students like us...)
Nene
Hey, did you heard about a ghost that appeared in our school？
No. Was it a rumor or something？
It wasn't a rumor. There were many eyewitnesses.
Not only did the students see it, but the teachers and the janitors saw it as well.
Eh？ Now that sounds interesting？ What kind of ghost is it？
This one looked like a girl about 3-4 years old. After school, she would appear at the backyard or some desolated places.
Could she be a kid in the neighborhood？
The teachers thought so, but there isn't any girl that looks like her in the neighborhood.
Then... What did that girl do？ Did she do something evil？
She didn't hurt anyone. She screamed and laughed with joy while running around the school...
That sounds weird. That doesn't fit an image of a ghost at all.
That's true.
Ah, right. People from the newspaper club had started the investigation. I might ask them.
Nene
Do you remember the story about a ghost that looked like a girl？
Yeah, I remember. Actually, I was interested in it. Did you get any more info？
Yeah. Somehow, the newspaper club's member met her. And I just talked with that member.
Did that member encounter the ghost？
Not a ghost. She was just a normal girl.
She was crying at the back of the swimming pool because she got lost from her friend.
What...？ Then she was actually a girl from the neighborhood, huh？
But there really isn't any girl with her description around here. In the end, the police came to pick her up.
Hmm, so we figured she wasn't a ghost, but another mystery appears.
The newspaper club will do the follow-up investigation.
(Investigation？ Students at our school easily get obsessed with some weird things...)
Nene
Hey, hey. I got more info about that girl. Wanna hear it？
Oh, I've been waiting for this. So, what is it？ Did you know where she came from？
Yeah. Well, she was actually from the nearby prefecture.
The nearby prefecture？ Eh？ But she's only 3 or 4 years old, right？
How did she come as far as our school？
Her mother was admitted in the hospital here. The girl visited her mother and sneaked out from the hospital.
So... She came to our school after she visited her mother？ But why did she do that？
Well... About that...
Her father would come to pick her up at night, so she came to our school to play while waiting for him.
Somehow this is not quite understandable. Anyhow, it was dangerous. That girl was alone, after all.
Yeah. I'm glad she didn't get into any accident.
Well, anyway. We can say that it's another case closed for this ghost story, right？
Nene
Hey, about the ghost story we've been talking about...
That story？ I think it's already solved, right？
That's right, but... Actually, there's a new finding about that girl.
A new finding？
Yeah, from what that girl said, when she sneaked out from the hospital, she had a friend accompanied her.
A friend？ Was it someone who went to visit the patient at the hospital？
No, it was an unknown boy.
He asked her to play with him. He looked lonely, so she decided to keep him company. But...
W-Wait, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲. Somehow I have a bad feeling about this...
At the hospital where that girl's mother was admitted, there was a seriously ill boy there...
W-Well, can we stop talking about this now？
According to that girl, the boy that sneaked out from the hospital with her looked exactly the same as that ill boy... Yeah...
When the member from the newspaper club found the girl, she said she got lost from her friend, right？
So, her story could be true...
I-I don't know！ I didn't hear this. I don't know！
Nene
Hey, have you ever been to the janitor's room？
I used to go there to borrow some cleaning tools.
So, you didn't see the interior, right？ There's a bed and a kitchen. You can spend a night there, you know？
Ah, I see. But how did you know？
Actually, the teacher asked me to go there, so I went there at times.
You were asked to go there？ Why？
The janitor's fingers were injured, so someone has to help him with the cooking.
Our janitor also has to prepare the food？ Don't tell me that's why ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ goes there...
The home economics teacher asked me to do that, so I couldn't refuse.
You are so kind, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲.
Is that so？ But I can also practice my cooking skills and sometimes I can cook something extra. It's rather helpful for me.
(Helpful？ What does she mean？ Does ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ eat food there too？)
Ah, by the way. Do you still have to help the janitor？
Nene
Yeah. Lately, I've been chatting with him about a lot of things.
Eh？ What kinds of topics do you talk about？
Things like music and movies. He knows a lot about movies so I really enjoy talking to him.
Music and... movies？ Eh？ That's quite unexpected.
Really？ I think it's just common.
But our janitor is quite an old man, right？
What are you talking about？ That was the previous janitor. The current one is a young guy, around 20 years old.
Eh！？ You should've told me earlier！
I think you didn't care about that.
Ah, could it be that you get worried？ It's okay. I have only you, all right？
(I'm worried...)
Nene
Hey, I have something to tell you.
What is it？
The janitor's injury has recovered, so I don't have to help him anymore.
I see... That's a relief.
Hehe. But it seems like the janitor really likes my food. He asked me to come to cook for him sometime.
...And what did you answer him？
I was thinking about taking his offer, but I'm sure you'll oppose.
Well... yeah.
So I refused. I told him I couldn't do it anymore and apologized to him.
Is that so...？ Phew.
Hehe. Was that a sigh of relief？ Geez. You should have faith in me. I really have only you.
Nene
About the janitor that we've talked about earlier...
Did anything happen after that？
No, nothing happened. But there's something new.
Something new？
Seems like the janitor talked about my food at the staff room. Now the teachers are anxious to taste my food.
No way...
I think they might ask me to cook for them. I don't know what to do if that happens.
That means you'll have to cook lots of food for them.
They'll pay me for the ingredients and probably give me some extra money too. Hey, shall I buy something for you？ Hehe.
Actually... You want to do it, right？
...Sorry. It's true about the teachers, but the rest was just a joke. Look how cute you are. I can't continue teasing you.
Nene
Lately, our school's new Seven Wonders have become very popular, you know？
New...？ What？
Come on. You've heard of them, right？ Like the ghost in the toilet, or the haunted stairs, or the moving biology model...
Ah, most schools have something like that.
Our school has them, too, but not the conventional ones. Currently, people are searching for the new Seven Wonders.
Really？ But, are the Seven Wonders something you can search for？
I doubt it. But, I feel like I want to support these people.
Why？
It's something that will spice up our school life, right？ And I think the original ghost stories are wonderful.
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ really likes this kind of thing, huh...？
Nene
The students who are searching for our school's new Seven Wonders have formed an association.
An association？
Yeah, "The New Seven Wonders Research Association." They hold meetings after school to discuss their plans.
If I say that they're just people who have too much free time, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ will probably get mad at me, right？
I'm not gonna get mad at you. I'll just think that you have no dream.
Dream...？ You call that dream？
It's more like ambition than dream. I'd say that you need some ambition to look into mysteries.
Hmm, I guess that's true.
I was thinking about joining them...
...Somehow, I kind of expected you'd say that.
But I won't. I have the part-time job and I have to spend time with you...
So, I'll pass this time. Such a pity, huh？
Nene
Hey, about the New Seven Wonders Research Association... I think they've found something.
Already？
Not seven of them, but only one for now. There's a small flower bed at the school's backyard, right？
I didn't know that. We have a flower bed there？
Somebody built it a long time ago and it's always been neglected. But recently, it becomes clean and beautiful again.
Someone might be taking care of it, right？
...You think so too, huh？ Yeah, if it's like that, it can't be called one of the Seven Wonders.
Maybe a new transfer student who loves flowers？
I wonder. Has someone been taken care of it？ I'm curious now. I'd better look into the matter.
Anyway, you really like this kind of story, huh？
Nene
Do you remember the flower bed we talked about last time？
Yeah, I remember. Someone has been taken care of it, right？
Well, I already knew who did that. It was just a coincidence, but I saw it.
Eh？ So who did it？
It's exactly as you said before.
There's a new transfer student who loves flowers and couldn't stand it that the flower bed was neglected.
Most girls are like that, huh？ Well, what kind of girl is this transfer student, then？
You've misunderstood it somehow. He's a guy.
A guy！？
There are guys who love flowers, too. And he's very cute. When I saw him, I felt like something was tickling my heart.
Umm, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲...
Hehe. Don't worry. I already have you.
But if it wasn't for you, I probably couldn't resist hugging him.
(Hey, can you not say that...？ Geez.)
Nene
Hey, we talked about the tea house earlier. Did you remember？
Yeah, there was a teacher who taught tea ceremony and flower arranging to female students, right？
Yeah, and you know that our judo club has a straw-matted room, right？ That's where the tea house used to be.
The tea house has become a martial arts room？ That's an extreme change.
But the one in charge of the judo club now is a female teacher.
Huh？ A female teacher？
She used to be a national judo player. She said that for judo, you have to learn the etiquettes as well as the moves.
...So, does she gather female students and teach them？
It's not restricted to female students, but no male student has ever joined. That's weird. She's such a pretty woman.
But it's judo. No matter how pretty she is, guys would feel awkward to learn from her.
I think that might be the reason... Hehe. Boys are interesting.
Nene
Hey, I told you about the female teacher who teaches judo, right？
Yeah, I remember that.
What do you think about girls who learn judo？
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ wants to learn judo, too？
Not really. But many girls learn martial arts for self-defense, right？ I think that's such a good idea.
Really...？ But to think about it, there are also a lot of female police officers, right？
Police officers have to go through special trainings. A smattering of knowledge can be a dangerous thing, okay？
Don't try to sound cool. Anyway, I think it's a good idea. You should at least be able to protect yourself.
It'd be worse if I tried to fight back and ended up provoking the attacker. I'd rather have someone protect me instead.
...Are you trying to put me under pressure？
Well, sort of. But you don't have to go as far as to learn any martial arts. It'd be bad if you got injured from that.
Nene
Hey, did you know？ The female police officers will come to our school to teach self-defense.
Eh？ Is that so？
Yeah, but the class is for female students only. They'll teach us some basic stuff.
Just hearing that makes me feel like ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ will become much stronger.
Hehe. I might be able to block someone from getting away from me.
...Hmm, I think you can do that.
Ah, really？ If I learn some martial arts techniques, I can do something like that. I see, I see.
(I think she got some wrong idea...)
Nene
Earlier, I attended a self-defense class.
Ah, how was it？
I learned a lot of things. But I think self-defense isn't something a novice can master easily.
Well, that's normal.
The police officer said that it'd be dangerous to fight recklessly. The best thing for us to do is to call for help.
I see.
She also said that I should find a nice boyfriend and ask him to accompany me all the time. She's funny.
And what did you tell her, ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲？
I told her it would be up to my boyfriend then.
Hmm... Which means I'll have to become stronger...
That's the ideal. But I love you the way you are now.
In case something happened, we both could run and call for help together.
That's... a little uncool...
By the way, any updates on the New Seven Wonders Research Association？
Nene
Ah, I think they've started their activities...
I wonder if they can find anything.
Well... They had stopped trying to find something. Now, they're trying to create something instead.
Create something？
They're trying to create our school's Seven Wonders and pass them on to students in the next generation.
I see... But their mission must have changed then.
Yeah. It's not researching but creating now. They even asked me once whether I got any subject for them.
Hmm？ Do you plan to come up with something for them？
No... I have some idea, but I'll feel like I'm cheating if I make up the Seven Wonders by myself. It's not challenging...
Nene
Do you remember that we talked about the New Seven Wonders Research Association last time？
Yeah, but I think ▲姉ヶ崎＊▲ wasn't much interested in it, right？
Yeah. And I already refused to join the group.
I see. But it seems pretty fun.
I was interested in it, but I think it would be better if those people chose the orthodox way.
Orthodox？
The Seven Wonders are something to remind us of our school, right？ The important thing is that they should be unique.
Hmm？ What do you mean？
Most schools also have the haunted stairs or the moving biology model, right？ What if we have something different？
Ah, I see. In that case, people will spread the rumors about our school's mysteries. Soon they will become the Seven Wonders.
I'd say that it's such a pity because I already thought up seven stories...
(...You already thought about them？)
Nene
The New Seven Wonders Research Association will be dissolved.
Really？
Yeah, parents of the most active student in the group found out that their kid borrowed many occult books from the library.
Ah...
The parents got worried and then they found out about the association...
Things like that happen a lot.
The research association isn't an official club, so our school can't do anything much to help.
I see. That's really bad.
Although I don't want to join them, I think they're nice and hard-working people. This is such a shock.
Well, it can't be helped. Adults also have their concerns.
Hah... Adult's concerns, huh？ Now I want to scream "I don't want to become an adult！" out loud.
Nene
Hey, have you heard？
About what？
In the end, the New Seven Wonders Research Association didn't have to be dissolved.
Eh？ Really？
Yeah. The Modern Japanese teacher helped them and offered to be the group's advisor himself.
Hmm. We have such a dedicated teacher here too.
But they had to change the group's name.
Because they wouldn't be researching the Seven Wonders anymore.
I see. So, have they decided on the new name？
The "Urban Legend Lovers Association."
Haha... What is that？
Isn't it good？ If it's urban legend, they can make up something. I'm thinking about offering my ideas to them, too.
Nene
...Hah.
What's wrong？
I think it's really hard to date a younger guy.
Did I do something bad to you？
Eh？ ...Ah, no. It's just that my friend had a fight with her boyfriend.
Is that so？ ...You scared me.
Sorry. But she's my friend so I'm quite worried. I hope they can reconcile.
What was the cause of their fight？
I haven't asked her yet... But it seems like they had a big quarrel during their date.
Is that so...？ So bad it happened during a date...
Right？ Hah... She's my close friend so I'm quite worried...
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲. You don't look well. Are you okay？
Nene
Hmm... Sorry. There's something that worries me.
If you want to talk, I can listen to you.
What should I do...？
I might not be of any help, but at least I can listen to your problem.
Well... Actually, it's about the friend I talked about before.
Ah... The one who got in a fight with her boyfriend？
Yeah... They finally broke up. Now, they didn't even want to see each other's face.
Is that so？
They used to be so sweet that I even got jealous of them. Just one fight and they broke up. ...I'll have to be careful, too.
Nene
Hey, can I ask you a question？
What is it？
How many friends do you have that are girls？
Friends that are girls？
Yeah, it's impossible to have none, right？ At least there must be some girls you're close to in class.
Well, I rarely talk to them. At most I just take a look at their homework, but I wouldn't call them my close friends...
I see.
Well, let me tell you this first. I don't mind at all if you get close to those girls.
I talked to my friend earlier and she quarreled with her boyfriend because of this issue. She got mad because a girl called him.
I see.
If you have any female friends, just tell me and I won't get mad at you. This is something I want you to know.
▲姉ヶ崎＊▲, somehow you look so happy.
Nene
Really？ One of my worries has gone... Well, it's about my friend.
Umm, is it the friend who quarreled with her boyfriend earlier？
Yeah, right. She got back on her feet and she already has a new boyfriend now.
Eh？ Is that so？
And her new boyfriend is another underclassman. It's amazing, although I think she didn't learn her lesson.
Was it just a coincidence？
No. She told me herself that she preferred younger guys. She's a gentle girl, so maybe her maternal instinct is strong.
Hmm. So, is that how it is？
Eh？ I can sense something from that. Do you feel like I'm not gentle？ Am I a mean girl who always teases you？
No, not at all... I'm sorry.
Geez, don't apologize. I was just joking. ...So cute▼
Nene
By the way, we talked about the Urban Legend Lovers Association before, right？
